1 Download ISO http://old-releases.ubuntu.com/releases/6.06.0/ Then Select Desktop CD Then Download Which architecture (NOT 64-bit PC AMD64)
2 Flash The ISO From USB Stick
3 Then When on installer menu enter Start or install ubuntu
4 Login To Desktop
5 Run sudo nano /etc/lsb-release
  Then change DISTRIB_ID=Ubuntu To DISTRIB_ID=Syslack Linux
  Then change DISTRIB_RELEASE=6.06 To DISTRIB_RELEASE=1.0
  Remove DISTRUB_CODENAME=dapper
  Then Change DISTIB_DESCRIPTION="Ubuntu 6.06.1 LTS" To DISTRIB_DESCRIPTION="Syslack Linux"
6 Go To Theme Preferences Then Select Clearlooks Instead Of Human
7 Open sessions then Disable Show splash screen on login then Enable Automatically save changes to session
8 Run sudo nano /boot/grub/menu.lst then change timeout 3 to 5 then add # on hiddenmenu example # hiddenmenu
  on End Default Options Change title Ubuntu To Syslack Linux On Every Beginning Even recovery mode and memtest86+ then remove quiet splash
  never update grub because you don’t actually need to run sudo update-grub since Syslack Linux For Legacy x86 32 bit,Mac (PowerPC) and IBM-PPC (POWER5),SPARC,HP PA-RISC,IA-64 uses grub legacy Which GRUB legacy reads menu.lst directly at boot, so changes take effect immediately.
9 Run sudo nano /etc/issue then change Ubuntu 6.06.1 LTS \n \l To Syslack Linux \n \l
  Then change sudo nano /etc/issue.net then change Ubuntu 6.06.1 LTS To Syslack Linux
10 Run sudo nano /etc/gdm/gdm.conf then add # On GraphicalTheme=Human And remove # On GraphicalThemes=circles/:happygnome Example #GraphicalTheme=Human And GraphicalThemes=circles/:happygnome
   Ctrl x y enter
11 Run sudo rm /etc/motd
